<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-130-556  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 130 556.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CAD-CAM International  Feb 1989 v8 n2 p31(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Leonardo: solid modeller. (Leonardo da Vinci, Hayward Gallery,London) (Preview)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Jones, Mike.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Leonardo da Vinci exhibition, running from Jan 26 to Apr 16 atthe Hayward Gallery in London, relates Leonardo's theories tomodern-day solid modeling and rendering techniques.andP;  According toDr Philip Steadman, dir of the Centre of Configurational Studiesat the Open University, 'Leonardo covers the same subjects, and inmuch the same order, as one would expect to find in a modernmanual of computer graphics.' Dr Peter Quarendon, who headsgraphics research at IBM's UK Scientific Centre agrees, sayingthat in some areas - ray tracing, for example - da Vinci's theoryis very close to that of computer graphics.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Leonardo da Vinci (exhibition)Computer-Aided DesignSolids ModelingComputer GraphicsArtArchitecture.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>